I would like to add support for the following syntax for `_.filter`:

> _.filter(collection, {'property': ['value1', 'value2',  'value3']});

This is similar to the [`__in` filter in django](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.10/ref/models/querysets/#in) as it would allow filtering a collection by items with a property that matches one of *several* values. Currently the `_.iteratee` shorthand only supports single value lookups. The behavior I'm describing can be accomplished easily enough with a custom `func` like so:

> _.filter(collection, item => _.includes(['value1', 'value2', 'value3'], item['property']));

... but this is a fairly common operation and (warning opinion ahead) I think the former syntax is cleaner. 

If I put together a PR that adds support for this feature would you consider it?

